The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has reaffirmed its commitment to conduct the governorship elections in Edo and Ondo states as planned amid the COVID-19 pandemic in the country. This comes as the electoral umpire expressed readiness to resume engagements with political parties, civil society groups, the media and other stakeholders in relation to the polls. INEC National Commissioner and Chairman, Information and Voter Education Committee, Festus Okoye, in a statement yesterday in Abuja, however, said modalities for the engagements would be made public on the 14th of this month. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .